    <section class=3D"faq" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/FA=
QPage">
      <h2 id=3D"faq" class=3D"text-center">Questions &amp; answers about em=
ail verification</h2>
      <p class=3D"text-center">Everything you need to know about how and wh=
y checking email addresses.</p>

      <div id=3D"accordion-general" class=3D"accordions">
        <div class=3D"card" itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=
=3D"https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class=3D"card-header accordionpointer collapsed" id=3D"headi=
ng1" data-toggle=3D"collapse" data-target=3D"#collapse1">
            <h3 itemprop=3D"name" class=3D"title-3 font-semibold mb-0" aria=
-expanded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"collapse1">How to use our email checker=
?</h3>
            <span class=3D"faq-expander"></span>
          </div>
          <div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemtype=3D"https=
://schema.org/Answer" id=3D"collapse1" class=3D"collapse" aria-labelledby=
=3D"heading1" data-parent=3D"#accordion-general">
            <div class=3D"card-body" itemprop=3D"text">
              Email checker is a free, easy to use and simple tool. Just en=
ter the email address and click on "Verify". We will then proceed with seve=
ral checks to verify the
              email address and flag it as valid or invalid.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class=3D"card" itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=
=3D"https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class=3D"card-header accordionpointer collapsed" id=3D"headi=
ng2" data-toggle=3D"collapse" data-target=3D"#collapse2">
            <h3 itemprop=3D"name" class=3D"title-3 font-semibold mb-0" aria=
-expanded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"collapse2">What is an email validator?<=
/h3>
            <span class=3D"faq-expander"></span>
          </div>
          <div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemtype=3D"https=
://schema.org/Answer" id=3D"collapse2" class=3D"collapse" aria-labelledby=
=3D"heading2" data-parent=3D"#accordion-general">
            <div class=3D"card-body" itemprop=3D"text">
              An email validator is a free tool to verify email addresses. =
It performs checks to validate that an email address is well formed, not fr=
om a disposable email service and that the
              email address is technically well-configured (MX records are =
present, SMTP mailbox replies successfully). In case it detects something w=
rong, the email address will
              be flagged as invalid.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class=3D"card" itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=
=3D"https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class=3D"card-header accordionpointer collapsed" id=3D"headi=
ng3" data-toggle=3D"collapse" data-target=3D"#collapse3">
            <h3 itemprop=3D"name" class=3D"title-3 font-semibold mb-0" aria=
-expanded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"collapse3">How does an email verifier w=
ork?</h3>
            <span class=3D"faq-expander"></span>
          </div>
          <div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemtype=3D"https=
://schema.org/Answer" id=3D"collapse3" class=3D"collapse" aria-labelledby=
=3D"heading3" data-parent=3D"#accordion-general">
            <div class=3D"card-body" itemprop=3D"text">
              <p>Email checker proceeds with several checks to determine if=
 an email address is valid:</p>
              <ol>
                <li>The email address must be well formed (e.g. {firstname.=
lastname}@{domain}).</li>
                <li>It should not be generated by a disposable email servic=
e (such as <code>mailinator.com</code>).</li>
                <li>The MX records should be present on DNS.</li>
                <li>An SMTP server should run for the domain.</li>
                <li>A mailbox with that email address should exist on the S=
MTP server.</li>
              </ol>
              <p>Depending on the provided email address, we might apply ex=
tra-checks on a per basis.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class=3D"card" itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=
=3D"https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class=3D"card-header accordionpointer collapsed" id=3D"headi=
ng4" data-toggle=3D"collapse" data-target=3D"#collapse4">
            <h3 itemprop=3D"name" class=3D"title-3 font-semibold mb-0" aria=
-expanded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"collapse4">Is Email Checker Free?</h3>
            <span class=3D"faq-expander"></span>
          </div>
          <div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemtype=3D"https=
://schema.org/Answer" id=3D"collapse4" class=3D"collapse" aria-labelledby=
=3D"heading4" data-parent=3D"#accordion-general">
            <div class=3D"card-body" itemprop=3D"text">
              <p>Email Checker is totally free to use. Mailmeteor makes it =
available to anyone interested in checking an email address and make sure y=
ou won't get a bounce.</p>
              <p>
                If you have large volume and/or want to verify multiple ema=
ils in batch, check out our <a href=3D"https://workspace.google.com/marketp=
lace/app/email_verifier_for_google_sheets/473712035382">Email Verifier for =
Google Sheets add-on</a>. It lets you verify email addresses in
                bulk, directly in Google Sheets.
              </p>
              <p>We also partnered with some companies to offer you exclusi=
ve discounts. Feel
                free to grab your discount <a href=3D"https://dashboard.mai=
lmeteor.com/account/partners">right from our partners page</a>.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class=3D"card" itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=
=3D"https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class=3D"card-header accordionpointer collapsed" id=3D"headi=
ng5" data-toggle=3D"collapse" data-target=3D"#collapse5">
            <h3 itemprop=3D"name" class=3D"title-3 font-semibold mb-0" aria=
-expanded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"collapse5">How many email verifications=
 can I perform per day?</h3>
            <span class=3D"faq-expander"></span>
          </div>
          <div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemtype=3D"https=
://schema.org/Answer" id=3D"collapse5" class=3D"collapse" aria-labelledby=
=3D"heading5" data-parent=3D"#accordion-general">
            <div class=3D"card-body" itemprop=3D"text">
              We apply a fair-use policy, so you are free to manually use E=
mail Checker as long as you don't abuse of it. Any abuse includes, but is n=
ot limited to, making
              automatic requests to our service.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class=3D"card" itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=
=3D"https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class=3D"card-header accordionpointer collapsed" id=3D"headi=
ng6" data-toggle=3D"collapse" data-target=3D"#collapse6">
            <h3 itemprop=3D"name" class=3D"title-3 font-semibold mb-0" aria=
-expanded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"collapse6">Can I verify emails in batch=
?</h3>
            <span class=3D"faq-expander"></span>
          </div>
          <div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemtype=3D"https=
://schema.org/Answer" id=3D"collapse6" class=3D"collapse" aria-labelledby=
=3D"heading6" data-parent=3D"#accordion-general">
            <div class=3D"card-body" itemprop=3D"text">
              <p>
                Email checker lets you verify one email address at a time. =
If you have large volume and/or want to verify multiple emails in batch, yo=
u should definitely check out
                a third-party solution, such as <a href=3D"https://withlove=
.usebouncer.com/mailmeteor" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow">Bouncer</a=
>,
                <a href=3D"https://clearout.io/" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer=
 nofollow">Clearout</a>,
                <a href=3D"https://www.emailable.com/" rel=3D"noopener nore=
ferrer nofollow">Emailable</a>,
                <a href=3D"https://neverbounce.com/" rel=3D"noopener norefe=
rrer nofollow">Neverbounce</a> or
                <a href=3D"https://www.zerobounce.net/" rel=3D"noopener nor=
eferrer nofollow">Zerobounce</a>.
              </p>
              <p>
                We partnered with those companies to offer you exclusive di=
scounts. Feel free to grab your discount
                <a href=3D"https://dashboard.mailmeteor.com/account/partner=
s">right from our partners page</a>.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class=3D"card" itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=
=3D"https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class=3D"card-header accordionpointer collapsed" id=3D"headi=
ng7" data-toggle=3D"collapse" data-target=3D"#collapse7">
            <h3 itemprop=3D"name" class=3D"title-3 font-semibold mb-0" aria=
-expanded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"collapse7">Does email checker use my da=
ta?</h3>
            <span class=3D"faq-expander"></span>
          </div>
          <div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemtype=3D"https=
://schema.org/Answer" id=3D"collapse7" class=3D"collapse" aria-labelledby=
=3D"heading7" data-parent=3D"#accordion-general">
            <div class=3D"card-body" itemprop=3D"text">
              <p>
                Your data stays yours - <i>like all products made by Mailme=
teor</i>. Email addresses that you verify using our email checker are not s=
aved by us nor shared with a
                third-party. Although, we might temporarily log requests ma=
de to the service for maintenance purposes.
              </p>
              <p>
                With this said, this page has Google Analytics. Consequentl=
y, the Google
                <a href=3D"https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel=3D"noop=
ener" target=3D"_blank">Privacy Policy</a>
                and
                <a href=3D"https://policies.google.com/terms" rel=3D"noopen=
er" target=3D"_blank">Terms of Service</a>
                apply.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class=3D"card" itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=
=3D"https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class=3D"card-header accordionpointer collapsed" id=3D"headi=
ng8" data-toggle=3D"collapse" data-target=3D"#collapse8">
            <h3 itemprop=3D"name" class=3D"title-3 font-semibold mb-0" aria=
-expanded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"collapse8">What to do once an email is =
verified?</h3>
            <span class=3D"faq-expander"></span>
          </div>
          <div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemtype=3D"https=
://schema.org/Answer" id=3D"collapse8" class=3D"collapse" aria-labelledby=
=3D"heading8" data-parent=3D"#accordion-general">
            <div class=3D"card-body" itemprop=3D"text">
              Once you have verified a list of valid email addresses, you c=
an send a highly personalized email campaign using Gmail with <a href=3D"ht=
tps://mailmeteor.com/">Mailmeteor</a>. Mailmeteor
              lets you send mass emails in Gmail that feel personal. It's t=
he most popular <a href=3D"https://mailmeteor.com/mail-merge/gmail">Gmail m=
ail merge</a> tool, Trusted by 6 million people
              worldwide for its simplicity and privacy focus.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</main>


